    {
      "number": 6,
      "id": "I_kwDONMXNnM6eKEmt",
      "title": "When was IPV6_DONTFRAG on macOS dual-stack sockets fixed?",
      "url": "https://github.com/marten-seemann/draft-seemann-tsvwg-udp-fragmentation/issues/6",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "marten-seemann",
      "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "I remember that IPV6_DONTFRAG didn't cause the DF bit to be set. We just recently investigated this in quic-go: https://github.com/quic-go/quic-go/issues/3793.\r\n\r\nMaybe we messed up back then, or maybe this was fixed quite recently. If it's the latter, it's probably worth calling this out in the draft.",
      "createdAt": "2024-11-12T22:01:31Z",
      "updatedAt": "2024-11-12T22:01:31Z",
      "closedAt": null,
      "comments": []
    },
    {
      "number": 7,
      "id": "I_kwDONMXNnM6eKE_t",
      "title": "Apple Network.framework",
